<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Universiade Swimming Tournament Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MESSINA, Sicily, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The swimming tournament of
the 19th World University Games ended here on Sunday with Japan
winning 9 gold medals.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese swimming team took their last gold medal in the
women's 100 meters backstroke final through Noriko Inada who clocked
1:02.24.
</P>
<P>
The United States won two golds on Sunday as Katherine A. Taylor
won the women's 50 meters freestyle and the men's relay team took the
title of the 4X100 meters medley relay.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's another gold went to Nathan Rickard of Australia who beat
his Italian opponent Lorenzo Vismara to the second place in the men's
50 meters freestyle.
</P>
<P>
The swimming games ended with Japan on top of the medal table. They
won 9 gold, 4 silver and 4 bronze medals.
</P>
<P>
The United States finished second with 8 gold medals, but they got
5 more silver and 6 more bronze medals than the Japanese.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine placed third with 4 gold and one silver medals, followed by
Slovakia with 4 gold medals.
</P>
<P>
The six-day swimming tournament only had a new Universiade record.
Most of the title-winning times were far behind world records and
Universiade records.
</P>
<P>
World swimming powerhouses Australia, the United States and Russia
didn't send their best swimmers to the Universiade while China didn't
send any swimmers to the tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
