<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Intl Building Federation Workers to Meet in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe will next week host the
International Federation of Building and Wood Workers (IFBWW)
20th congress which is scheduled to focus on the trade union
movement's role in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The congress, whose theme is ''modernizing our union'', is
expected to attract 400 delegates. It runs from September 3 to 5.
</P>
<P>
''Discussions will focus on the need for trade unions to adapt
and strengthen their position to best meet workers' needs in
modern societies which are increasingly influenced by changing
political/economical circumstances and growing globalization,''
said an IFBWW statement today.
</P>
<P>
IFBWW, with a membership of 13 million drawn from 264 trade
unions in 110 countries, promotes international solidarity, human
and trade union rights.
</P>
<P>
Women's participation at this year's congress has risen to
12.5 percent, up from 11 percent during the last congress in
1993. Gender issues are also part of the congress agenda, the
statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
