<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Leaves for Pretoria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- President Yoweri Museveni left
here today for Pretoria of South Africa where he will attend
talks between Uganda and Sudan brokered by South African
President Nelson Mandela.
</P>
<P>
Museveni who was seen off at the Entebbe International Airport
near Kampala, capital of Uganda by Vice President and
Agricultural Minister Specioza Kazibwe, is accompanied by First
Deputy Premier and Minister of Foreign Affairs Eriya Kategaya.
</P>
<P>
Neighboring Uganda and Sudan broke off diplomatic ties in 1995
and have since denounced each other for supporting rebels in the
other countries against their governments.
</P>
<P>
The South African Foreign Affairs Department in a statement
said the two-day meeting would be held at Mandela's official
residence starting today and it would also be attended by
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe in his capacity as chairman of
the Organization for African Unity.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was arranged to enable Museveni and Sudanese
President Omar el-Bashir "to discuss sensitive issues," the
statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
