<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Injures 4 in N. Somali Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Four children were injured,
one very critical, after fire gushed their makeshift huts in the
eastern quarter of Bossaso, a northern town in Somalia on
Saturday, reports reaching here today said.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports, the fire had destroyed 250 huts and
houses, displacing as many as 700 people who lived in the area
mainly inhabited by refugees.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities in the region characterized the incidents
as terrifying accident. The elders attributed the reason for
the fire to the strong winds of the Northwest Monsoon which
hits the coastal regions of Somalia at this time every year.
</P>
<P>
A radio operator in Bossaso said that the fire began from an
uncovered fire outside a hut used for cooking. The strong winds
then blew the fire which caught the same hut and spread further
to the adjacent houses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
