<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Urges Africans to Work for Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) Salim Ahmed Salim has called
on Africans to re-dedicate themselves to the unity of the
continent for proper development.
</P>
<P>
"The development of culture should embrace important elements
such as tolerance, reconciliation and the culture of peace,"
Salim said, quoted by the News Agency of Nigeria today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the third Pan-African Historical Theater Festival
on Saturday in Cape Coast, Ghana, Salim said that all elements of
the society, especially women, must be properly integrated for
the realization of genuine cultural development of the continent.
</P>
<P>
According to Salim, the OAU has been doing everything possible
to promote African culture.
</P>
<P>
Through the organization, a lot of important cultural
declarations had been fulfilled, he noted, adding that the OAU
had continued to render support to cultural programs both at
regional and continental levels.
</P>
<P>
Salim also commended Africans for resisting to adopt foreign
culture.
</P>
<P>
The 10-day festival, which began on Saturday, has attracted
more than 10 countries including the United States and Jamaica.
</P>
<P>
Activities lined up for the event include inter-denominational
church service, carnivals, exhibitions, five-day Pan-African
colloquium, bazaar and youth-day program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
