<HEADLINE> Divorces Rise 9.1 Percent in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
TEHRAN, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Iran recorded a 9.1 percent rise
in divorce cases in the first quarter of the current Iranian calendar
year starting from March 21 over that of last year, a government
agency said here today.
</P>
<P>
More than 8,600 divorce cases were registered in the period, the
country's Statistics and Registration Administration said. But it
did not elaborate the causes for the rise.
</P>
<P>
Specialists attribute the high divorce rate to economic
pressures as incomes are very low and inflation reaching 50-70
percent yearly.
</P>
<P>
A woman specialist said about 80 to 90 percent of the women are
not satisfactory with their marriage not only for economic reasons
but for the negligence of their husbands as well.
</P>
<P>
According to the government agency, more than 130,000 couples
got married in the first quarter, up 4 percent from that in
the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
