<HEADLINE> Mandela Expresses Condolence on Death of Princess </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 31 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Nelson Mandela today expressed "profound shock and deepest
sympathy" at the death of Britain's Princess Diana.
</P>
<P>
In a message to British Queen Elizabeth ii, Mandela said, "on
behalf of the government and people of South Africa, i would like
to express profound shock and deepest sympathy at the untimely
passing of Diana.
</P>
<P>
"She will be sadly missed as a warm, compassionate and caring
person," Mandela said, noting that "Diana had indeed become an
ambassador for victims of land mines, war orphans, the sick and
needy throughout the world."
</P>
<P>
Diana, 36, died in a hospital early today after a car crash,
which happened last night at a Paris road tunnel under the Alma
bridge on the Seine River bank.
</P>
<P>
Her companion Egyptian millionaire Dodi el-Fayed, 41, and the
driver were killed outright. Her bodyguard was also seriously
injured. 
</P>
