<HEADLINE> Assad Discusses Mideast Peace With EU Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
DAMASCUS, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez Assad
here today discussed the Middle East peace process with the visiting
Middle East envoy of the European Union Miguel Angel Moratinos.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, attended by Syrian Freign Minister Farouk Shara,
Assad also discussed with Moratinos the international efforts to
overcome the obstacles put by the Israeli government, according to
a presidential spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that Assad had stressed the importance of an
active European role in the peace efforts as well as Syria's
adherence to a just and comprehensive peace.
</P>
<P>
The EU envoy briefed the Syrian leader about the European
efforts to activate the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos met and held talks with Syrian Foreign Minister Shara
Saturday. He told the press after the talks that they mainly covered
the current state of the Middle East peace process, particularly
along the Syrian-Israeli track, and the related EU role.
</P>
<P>
Peace talks between Syria and Israel has been deadlocked since
February 1996. Damascus has refused to return to the negotiating
table unless Israel is ready to fully return the Syrian Golan
Heights which it captured in 1967 and annexed in 1981. 
</P>
</TEXT>
