<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fredericks, Devers Take 100m Titles at World Sprint Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Italy, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Namibia's Frank Fredericks
and Gail Devers of the United States respectively won the men's and
women's 100-meter races titles at the world sprint festival in the
Cibali Stadium here on Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
Fredericks, ranking third in the world this year, touched the
finishing line in 10.15 seconds. Americans Dennis Mitchell and John
Drummond took second and third places in 10.27 and 10.30.
</P>
<P>
In the women' 100m race, Devers, ranking 4th in the world this
year, beat world third-ranking Ukrainean Zhanna Pintusevich and other
rivals to win the trophy by timing 11.03 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Pintusevich finished second in 11.23 and Nigerian Endurance
Ojokolu was third in 11.28.
</P>
<P>
The 4th to 7th places in the men's race were Nigerian Osmond Ezinwa
in 10.33, Canadian Bruny Surin in 10.48, Deji Aliu of Nigeria in 10.52
and Italian Giovanni Puggioni in 10.60.
</P>
<P>
In the women's race, Russian Marina Trandenkova, Jamaicans Juliet
Cuthbert and Carlette Guidry, Russian Natalya Voronova and Italian
Giada Gallina ranked 4th to 8th in 11.42, 11.62, 11.65, 11.73 and
11.99.  
</P>
