<HEADLINE> Romanian Szabo Wrests Women's 1,500m Gold at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Italy, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Athen world championships
3,000-meter gold winner Romanian Gabriela Szabo captured the women's
1,500m gold medal at the Universiade athletics competition which
closed at Cibali Stadium here on Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
Szabo clocked four minutes 10.31 seconds, only 0.09 seconds faster
than Portugal's Carla Sacramento, the world championships gold
medallist in this event. Sacramento took the silver in 4:10.40 and
Lidia Chojecka of Poland was third in 4:12.38.
</P>
<P>
The men's 1,500m champion went to the Briton Anthony Whiteman who
was timed in three minutes 43.57 seconds. Carlos Garcia of Spain
was the runner-up in 3:43.97.
</P>
<P>
In the men's long jump final, Athen world championships gold
medallist Cuban Ivan Pedreso won the title with 8.40 meters in the
sixth and last jump, ahead of Jamaican James Beckford (8.35m) and
Slovenian Gregor Cankar (8.11m).
</P>
<P>
Out of the 11 gold medals on offer today, The Americans took
four golds.
</P>
<P>
The United States wrested the men's and women's 4x100-meter relay
gold medals with 38.48 seconds and 44.04 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The silver medals of the two events went to the Cuban team (38.52)
and Russian team (44.37) seperately.
</P>
<P>
The American men's team clocked three minutes 02.53 seconds for the
men's 4x400m relay champion. The Jamaican team finished second in
3:02.68.
</P>
<P>
American Amy Acuff picked up the women's high jump gold with 1.98
meters, followed by Romanian Monica Iagar (1.96m) and Marie
Collonville of France (1.94m).
</P>
<P>
The men's and women's half marathon titles went to Brazialian
Marison Santos who was timed in one hour 03 minutes and 32 seconds and
Japanese Mari Sotani who chalked up one hour 11 minutes and 49
seconds. Kenyan Mayaka Stephine and Italian Agata Balsamo were
runners-up with 1:03'51 and 1:13'06.
</P>
<P>
The Russian team took the women's 4x400m relay gold with three
minutes and 27.93 seconds, ahead of the Cuban team (3:29.00) and the
British team (3:30.57).
</P>
<P>
German Mark Ostendarp snatched the men's 3,000m steeplechase
champion with eight minutes 25.83 seconds. the Netherlands team
finished second and the Austrian team came third.
</P>
<P>
After six days of competition, The United States topped the gold
medal standing with eight golds.
</P>
<P>
The second to fourth places were Russia (6 golds), Ukraine (5
golds) and Cuba (4 golds).
</P>
<P>
Romania, Germany, South Africa, Britain, Belarus and Nigeria won
tow gold medals each.
</P>
<P>
Ten countries took one gold each and other 14 countries took
silvers and bronzes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
