<HEADLINE> Chinese, Maltese Foreign Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and
Minister of Foreign Affairs Qian Qichen held talks with his
Maltese counterpart George Vella here today.
</P>
<P>
During the talks at the Diaoyutai State Guest House, the two
sides made a positive review of Sino-Maltese relations. They
exchanged views on further promotion of bilateral cooperation in
such areas as politics, trade, economic affairs, culture, science,
technology and civil aviation, as well as on international issues
of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Qian noted that since China and Malta established diplomatic
relations 25 years ago, relations between the two countries have
been growing steadily.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two sides have forged a sound, mutually
beneficial relationship of cooperation on the basis of mutual
respect, equality and mutual benefits.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two sides have been supporting each other in
international affairs and share identical or similar views on many
international issues.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that the friendly cooperative relations
between the two countries enjoy a solid foundation and bright
prospects.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the Chinese people have always cherished
friendly feelings for the Maltese people. The two peoples had
similar sufferings in the past. Now they share common goals in
safeguarding world peace and stability, expanding their economies
and improving their living standards.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that the Chinese Government has always attached great
importance to developing friendly cooperative relations with
Malta. He said that China is ready to make concerted efforts with
the Maltese side to push the bilateral relations to a new level.
</P>
<P>
Vella, deputy prime minister, minister of foreign affairs and
minister of environment of Malta, said that Malta values relations
with China. It has been following with great interest the
tremendous achievements in economic affairs that China has made in
the past ten-plus years and its increasingly greater role in world
politics and economic affairs.
</P>
<P>
He expressed congratulations China on its success in resolving
the Hong Kong issue.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Maltese government is ready to discuss with
the Chinese side on possibilities in stepping up cooperation in
such fields as trade and economic affairs, the manufacturing
industry and the shipping industry, so as to further bilateral
friendly cooperative relations.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, officials of the two countries signed an
agreement on civil air transport and an executive program on
cultural cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
