<HEADLINE> Iranian President Raps Israel, US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami today attacked Israel and the United States for not
honoring the resolutions passed by the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
In his harshest statements on foreign policy issues ever
since his inauguration on August 4, Khatami referred to the
Israeli regime as "the greatest manifestation of international
terrorism."
</P>
<P>
Addressing family members of the Lebanese fighters killed in
combat against Israel, Khatami also criticized the United States
for not using its veto power at the U.N. to block Israeli
actions.
</P>
<P>
On the U.S. continued support for the Israeli regime, the 54-
year-old president noted that the interests of American nation
have been sacrificed for those of "the Zionist regime."
</P>
<P>
"With full arrogance, the Zionist regime is trampling all of
the resolutions of the United Nations and the Security Council,"
Khatami was quoted by the state-run Tehran Radio as saying.
</P>
<P>
"In many places, Israel has escaped the veto power of the
United States..." he said, adding that the U.S. government has
compromised the interests of the American nation in its effort
to protect the Israeli interests.
</P>
<P>
"It is really appalling to see that in today's world, because
of the mistaken policies of the U.S. administration, even the
interests and expedience of the American nation have been
sacrificed for the sake of a gang of racists (Israel) in the
world," Khatami said.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that "the U.S government must apologize to their
nation for its action."
</P>
<P>
Khatami said that Iran was not against peace in the Middle
East, a peace which everyone would enjoy.
</P>
<P>
He said that "we want peace for all, peace for the people of
Palestine, Syria, regional countries and other countries in the
world."
</P>
<P>
Khatami hinted that under his administration Iran would
continue its support for the Lebanese resistance movement
in southern Lebanon which has been fighting Israeli forces for
over a decade.
</P>
<P>
"We see resistance against aggressors as the right of all the
free nations in the world. Within the framework of revolutionary
and Islamic values, Islamic Republic of Iran would defend the
rights of these nations," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
