<HEADLINE> Greek Transport Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Greece's Transport and
Communications Minister, Haris Kastanidis, resigned today, Greek
government spokesman Dimitris Reppas announced.
</P>
<P>
He will be replaced by Undersecretary for the Interior, Public
Administration and Decentralization Tassos Mantelis, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
Reppas gave no reasons of Kastanidis' resignation, but added
that both Kastanidis' letter of resignation and Prime Minister
Costas Simitis' reply would be released later today.
</P>
<P>
Kastanidis reportedly tendered his resignation to Simitis last
weekend following local media reports that he was personally
reprimanded at a cabinet meeting last Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to Reppas, Simitis had made no reference to
individual ministers during the meeting, but had urged his
ministers collectively to show better coordination, cooperation
and solidarity.
</P>
<P>
Simitis today accepted Kastanidis' resignation after meeting
with him for an hour.
</P>
<P>
It is the first resignation of senior government minister since
Simitis took office in January 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
