<HEADLINE> Hang Seng London Index Adds New Constituent Stock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 1 (Xinhua) -- China Resources Enterprise
Ltd. will be included as a constituent stock of the Hang Seng
London Reference Index (HSLRI) from September 3, 1997, the HSI
Services Ltd. announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said the inclusion is in line with the
objective of compiling the HSLRI which is to monitor the price
movements of Hang Seng Index constituents traded in London after
the close of the Hong Kong market.
</P>
<P>
With the inclusion of China Resources Enterprise Ltd., there
will be 29 constituent stocks in the HSLRI, accounting for around
98 percent of the market capitalization of the Hang Seng Index.
</P>
