<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 1 (Xinhua) -- In the wake of last week's
plunge, share prices continued to decline on the Singapore market
as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index lost another 19.2
points to close at 1786.44 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank from last Friday to 256.66
million units, valued at 681.3 million Singapore dollars (about
451.19 million U.S. dollars). Declines continued to lead advances
by 227 to 144 while 235 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Magnum Corporation was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 13.21 million units. It was followed by
Super Coffeemix which had 12.46 million shares traded. Asia Food &AMP;
Property was next with 11.95 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Samanda Holdings led the gainers of the day as it rose by 65
cents to finish at 6.6 Singapore dollars. Rashid Hussain gained 60
cents to end at 4.32 Singapore dollars while the Singapore Bus
Foreign 500 increased by 55 cents to close at 7.4 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation
(OCBC) Foreign was the biggest loser as it declined by 1.4 dollars
to end at 10.4 Singapore dollars. The Development Bank of
Singapore (DBS) Foreign lost 1.2 dollars to close at 14.8
Singapore dollars while local property developer City Developments
was 1 dollar lower to finish at 8.55 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
