<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Achievement Exhibition to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A national exhibition has been
scheduled for September 7 to showcase a vast array of the
country's achievements since the 14th National Congress of the
Chinese Communist Party was held in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Represented at the event will be 64 departments under the State
Council and all provinces, autonomous regions, and municipalities,
making it the largest exhibition since New china was founded in
1949, Wang Chunzheng, vice-minister of the State Planning
Commission, said at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Exhibition Center, the site of the event, will be
divided into two sections, covering general and regional
displays. The interior exhibition section will cover 14,400 square
meters, and the exterior section, 4,000 sq m.
</P>
<P>
In the General Hall will be a series of displays depicting
outstanding accomplishments made by the Chinese people in
promoting ethical and cultural progress and material progress,
under the leadership by the Party Central Committee headed by
Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Its 17 exhibition areas will pay tribute to the reform of the
country's economic structure, opening-up, comprehensive national
strength, macro-economic control, ethnical and cultural progress,
and progress in introducing a legal system.
</P>
<P>
One exhibition area will show the development blueprint for the
next century.
</P>
<P>
Also on show will be large machines and other equipment
representing China's latest technological standards.
</P>
<P>
The Regional Hall will have 31 exhibit areas for depicting the
achievements scored by various provinces, autonomous regions, and
municipalities since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Bai Keming, deputy head of the Propaganda Department of the
Party Central Committee, said that the past five years have been
an "unusual period -- during which the economy has grown rapidly, and
all-round social progress was achieved."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese economy has entered a sound period of rapid growth
and low inflation, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the eve of the 15th Party National Congress, it is of great
significance for the Propaganda Department of the CPC Central
Committee, the State Planning Commission, the State Economic and
Trade Commission, the State Commission for Restructuring the
Economy, and the State Statistics Bureau to hold the event, Bai
noted.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is scheduled to close on October 5.  
</P>
</TEXT>
