<HEADLINE> 5 Tamil Rebels Killed in North Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Five Tamil rebels were killed
on Sunday in fighting with government forces in Northern Province
of Sri Lanka, according to military sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
rebels fired mortar at the troops manning defenses around
Puliyankulam Town.
</P>
<P>
The troops retaliated with mortar and artillery fire, killing
at least five rebels and injuring two others while three soldiers
were injured due to rebel mortar fire, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a war for a separate state
in the north and east of the country since 1983.
</P>
<P>
The government troops launched an operation on Puliyankulam
Town on August 19 in an effort to retake the highway linking the
government-held Vavuniya to Killinochchi further north, a vital
supply route to the North Jaffna Peninsula.  
</P>
</TEXT>
