<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ramos Increases Benefits for Pensioners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos today approved an 8-percent across-the-board rise in the
monthly pension of Social Security System (SSS) pensioners.
</P>
<P>
Ramos announced the increased benefits in his address during
the 40th anniversary celebration of the SSS.
</P>
<P>
The minimum monthly SSS pension for those who have at least 10
years of service will be raised from 1,000 pesos (33.3 U.S.
dollars) to 1,200 pesos (40 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Ramos also approved the increase from 1,200 pesos (40 dollars)
to 1,500 pesos (50 dollars) of the minimum monthly pension of SSS
pensioners who have rendered at least 20 years of service.
</P>
<P>
Beneficiaries of death and disability pensions, who were
getting the minimum monthly pension of 800 pesos (26.7 dollars),
will now receive 1,000 pesos (33.3 dollars).
</P>
<P>
"These benefits are integral to a vision that we hold of social
security for the Filipino," Ramos said as he vowed to keep working
for increased benefits for SSS members as government resources
would allow.
</P>
<P>
During the last 40 years, the SSS extended 127 billion pesos
(4.23 billion dollars) in benefits to its members and their
beneficiaries, of which 72 percent, or 91 billion pesos (3 billion
dollars), was delivered during the five years of the Ramos
administration.  
</P>
</TEXT>
