<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh PM Issues Foreign Investment Directives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina has issued a set of directives to the Board of
Investment (BOD) aimed at providing the best possible assistance
and support to foreign investors, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Under the directives, separate areas will be set aside for the
establishment of industrial estates for particular products.
"Haphazard growth of industries should be discouraged," Hasina
said.
</P>
<P>
The environmental aspects must be taken into account before a
new industry is allowed to be established, Hasina said. "The
environmental aspects must be spelled out by the entrepreneurs
before applying for permission to set up an industry," the prime
minister stressed.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of marking lands for setting up industrial parks
in the future, she said: "We must have a plan for using our lands
ensuring their utmost utilization."
</P>
<P>
She said a special immigration desk should be set up at the
airport so that no foreign investor is harassed in any way.
</P>
</TEXT>
