<HEADLINE> APS Claims Responsibility for Blast at Olympic Headquarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Anti-Power Struggle, a Greek
urban terrorist organization, today claimed responsibility for the
explosion Sunday night outside the headquarters of the National
Olympic Games Committee in Kolonaki, central Athens.
</P>
<P>
The police said today that the explosion caused a small fire,
but no one was injured.
</P>
<P>
An unidentified man called the Greek private television
state "Skai", claiming that the APS had set the explosive
mechanism, which was reportedly made of two gas canisters.
</P>
<P>
Athens is one of the five finalist cities bidding to host the
2004 Olympiad, together with Rome, Stockholm, Cape Town and Buenos
Aires.
</P>
<P>
The International Olympic Committee is to vote on September 5
to decide the winner. 
</P>
