<HEADLINE> Beijing-Singapore Adds One More Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Airlines Ltd. will
add one more flight per week to the air route from Beijing to
Singapore, according to the Civil Aviation Administration of China
(CAAC).
</P>
<P>
The Saturday SQ811 flight will take off at 8:40 am, with a
travel time of six hours and a quarter, the airline said. Other
SQ811 flights now run on Tuesday, Thursday, Friday, and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the number of business people and tourists
traveling between the two places has grown rapidly, leaving the
existing flight schedule unable to cater to demand, according to
the airline.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that the No. SQ811 will add another two morning
flights, on Monday and Wednesday, beginning on October 26.
