<HEADLINE> Three Million More People Have Access to TV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Some three million more people
in poverty-stricken areas have gained access to television thanks
to a charitable program targeting rural residents.
</P>
<P>
The program, aiming at improving cultural undertakings in the
countryside, has helped set up 240 satellite ground stations in
the poorest regions in China since it was launched three years ago.
</P>
<P>
The program is sponsored by the Committee for Relieving
Cultural Poverty and China Central Television.
</P>
<P>
Some 84.5 percent of the Chinese people now have access to
TV. However, people living in some remote and mountainous regions
still cannot receive TV signals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
