<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Price Index up in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The price index of commodities
and services in Vietnam rose slightly by 0.1 percent in August
compared with July and 3.6 percent over the same period of 1996,
the lowest record in the country in recent years, the General
Department of Statistics said today.
</P>
<P>
The price of foodstuff grew by 1.4 percent, while the prices of
non-food and services jumped to 4.5 and 9.2 percent respectively,
compared with July.
</P>
<P>
The price index increased 1.4 percent in the first eight months
of this year, mainly due to increases of prices of non-food and
foodstuff items and services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
