<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Air Force Recruits Female Pilots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Air Force will
train 37 more female pilots, the seventh group of women the
country has schooled in aeronautics since 1951, it was announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
The women are enrolled in the Changchun Flying Academy for a
one-year training course, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The oldest is 20, and the youngest is 17. They were chosen from
10,000 high school graduates in six provinces and one municipality.
</P>
<P>
The trainees will study mathematics, physics, computer science,
English, aviation theory and parachute jumping. After graduation,
the qualified candidates will enter academies for advanced courses
in flight and navigational skills.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion of their education, they will receive a
military bachelor degree and lieutenant rank.
</P>
<P>
China has the biggest number of female pilots in the
world. Some of them have become division or regimental commanders.
</P>
<P>
Chinese female pilots now fly both commercial planes and
fighter jets. The record flying time held by a Chinese female
pilot is 7,000 hours, sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
