<HEADLINE> Commercial Development of Waste Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- As a city of one million
residents, Kampala produces some 800 tonnes of garbage daily and
the sum will increase to 124,444 tonnes by the year 2004, The New
Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
Fred Mubiru, the refuse manager of Kampala, appealed to a
scaled commercial development of the waste.
</P>
<P>
In his document, "the solid waste disposal -- Kampala report",
Mubiru told a workshop on vermicomposting training that each
resident of Kampala generates 0.8 kilogram of waste a day.
</P>
<P>
According to his estimate, the total number of residents in
Kampala will increase to some 1,556,800 by 2004.
</P>
<P>
Kampala City Council (KCC) has a sector to deal with the waste
in the city, but KCC cannot handle the whole problem by its own
strength, the official noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
