<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-01 08:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Executes Spy for US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced here today
that it had executed a citizen spying for the United States
in a gesture of tough stance toward its 18-year-old enemy.
</P>
<P>
Tehran's Military Tribunal said in a statement that Siavosh
Bayani, son of Abolqassem, was hanged in the capital of Tehran
last week on charges of spying for "Great Satan, America."
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, which did not mention his age,
Bayani had relayed secret military information to the
U.S. intelligence service.
</P>
<P>
Bayani left Iran for the United State through a neighboring
country in the Iranian year 1363 (1984-85), where he applied for
political asylum.
</P>
<P>
After living in the United States for 11 years, the Central
Intelligency Agency (CIA) assigned him to return to Iran for
espionage activities, according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested in 1995 by the Iranian security forces
and later confessed to his activities -- "spying for Great
Satan, America," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Based on his confessions, Bayani received a sum of 1,000 to
1,500 U.S. dollars for each contact.
</P>
<P>
He was tried at a tribunal in Tehran and sentenced to death
according to a verdict issued on January 9, 1995.
</P>
<P>
The verdict was carried out at the Evin prison in Tehran last
week after going through the legal proceedings and being
endorsed by the Supreme Court.
</P>
<P>
Iran has passed a law with severe punishment -- death
sentence for those who spy for the United States and Israel
because Tehran regards the United States and Israel as their
sworn enemies.
</P>
<P>
The United States severed diplomatic relations with Iran in
1980 during the hostage-taking crisis but the election of
moderate President Mohammad Khatami prompted the
U.S. administration to consider whether the time was ripe for a
change in its approach to Tehran.
</P>
<P>
But, the Iranian authorities, especially Supreme Leader
Ali Khamenei, seem to continue their anti-U.S. policy and
declared earlier that it would have normal relations with all
countries except for the United States and Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
