<HEADLINE> 19 Persons Meted Death in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen criminals were
condemned to death in August in the Philippines, bringing to 453
the total number of death row inmates in the Bureau of
Corrections, the Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Of the 19, the report said, 11 were convicted of aggravated
rape, five of murder, two of aggravated robbery and one of drug
trafficking.
</P>
<P>
It said that there are now 238 condemned rapists in death row,
127 of whom abused either their own daughters or children below 12
years of age.
</P>
<P>
The rest of the inmates were convicted of murder, aggravated
robbery, kidnapping, drug trafficking, parricide and illegal
possession of firearm.
</P>
<P>
The inmates include six foreigners and seven females, it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
