<HEADLINE> Shanghai Invests More in Cultural Undertakings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai will invest 9.27
billion yuan (nearly 120 million US dollars) in the five years
ending 2000 to build more museums and theaters, sources said.
</P>
<P>
In the previous five years, Shanghai's investment in cultural
infrastructure was only four million yuan.
</P>
<P>
New buildings under construction include the Shanghai Grand
Theater, Shanghai Art Museum and Shanghai Book Park. The city has
already renovated most of its cultural centers at the neighborhood
communities.
</P>
<P>
The move is to make Shanghai famous not only as the biggest
commercial metropolis in China, but also an important
international cultural center, sources said. 
</P>
