<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Industrial Park Growing Fast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Japanese industrial park
in Dalian, a seaside city in Northeast China's Liaoning Province,
has attracted a total investment of 500 million US dollars in the
past four years.
</P>
<P>
Of the 33 enterprises already operational in the park, the
majority are ventures wholly-funded by Japanese corporations,
including a number of transnationals, such as Toto, Fuji Electric,
Mitsubishi Electric, YKK and Konica.
</P>
<P>
A senior manager with the park's development company said many
enterprises started production this year. He attributed the rapid
growth to the improving investment environment of the Dalian
Economic and Technological Development Zone, where the park is
located.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, 970,000 sq.m. of land has been transferred to
investors, covering more than half of the total transferable area.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese industrial park was established to commemorate the
20th anniversary of the normalization of Sino-Japanese
relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
