<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
drifted lower in lackluster trading today as overseas investors
move their attention to the turmoil on Asian equity and currency
markets.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 10 points lower at 2,446 with a turnover
of 42 million NZ dollars (27 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leaders, Air New Zealand was the only gainer, edging
up 1 cent to 282 cents.
</P>
<P>
Telecom and Carter Holt Harvey both held their ground, closing
at 772c and 324c respectively.
</P>
<P>
Other leaders all fell. Fletcher Paper dived 12c to 304c.
Brierley Investment dropped 2c to 132c. Lion Nathan slipped 3c to
392c.
</P>
<P>
There were 23 rises and 62 falls.  
</P>
