<HEADLINE> China Establishes National TV Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- China will present national
TV awards to best theatrical creations starting this year, sources
have announced.
</P>
<P>
The "China Golden Eagle Award" was established by a TV magazine
in 1983, but the country has turned it into a national honor in an
effort to encourage fine TV programs, they said.
</P>
<P>
The event will be sponsored by the Chinese Federation of
Literary and Art circles and the Chinese TV Artists Association,
instead of the former organizer "Popular TV Magazine."
</P>
<P>
TV viewers nationwide will vote on the best drama, documentary,
actress and actor.
</P>
<P>
China currently has an estimated 800 million TV viewers. 
