<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Women Assisted for Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian women,
particularly small scale operators, are getting help in running
business, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Tanzania Home Economics Association (TAHEA), Mwanza
Region, is scheduled to help launching a savings and credit
society to enable women in low and middle income bracket to
acquire loans easily and enhance their business activities.
</P>
<P>
"TAHEA Mwanza region will continue to assist all small scale
business communities by coordinating with potential donors for
assistance," said TAHEA regional coordinator Asia Kapande over
the weekend during the closing ceremony of a five-day workshop on
improvement of business skills to small scale women operators in
Mwanza.
</P>
<P>
Participants to the workshop are from those managing various
ventures, including food vending, garments designing, tailoring
and operating grocery.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Tanzania Women Organization (UWT) in Kilimajaro
Region has launched a massive poverty-alleviation campaign
through which women groups under it are mobilized to initiate
income generating projects.
</P>
<P>
Among the proposed and existing projects are saw-milling,
dairy farming, nursery schools, needlework, beauty salon, milling
machines, passenger bus services, etc. 
</P>
