<HEADLINE> United States Wins Americas Basketball Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Corey Beck hit 18 points to
lead the United States to a 95-86 victory over Puerto Rico Sunday
in the final of the Tournament of the Americas championship.
</P>
<P>
The United States team, made up of player from the the
Continental Basketball Association, had a 14-point at the interval.
</P>
<P>
But Puerto Rico rallied strongly in the start of the second
half with big effort from Jose Ortiz, who scored a game-high 26
points, to come within 2 points with just two minutes left before
the U.S. team hit back.
</P>
<P>
The United States qualifies automatically as reigning world
champion to the 1998 basketball world championship in Greece.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Sunday, Steve Nash scored 29 points as Canada beat Cuba
92-83 to obtain the fourth and final berth.
</P>
<P>
Argentina, Brazil and Puerto Rico had already booked their
tickets to the 1998 championship.
</P>
<P>
The final standings saw the United States on top, followed by
Puerto Rico, Brazil, Argentina and Canada.
</P>
<P>
In other action, Brazil came back from a halftime deficit to
beat Argentina 76-75 in playoff for the third place.
</P>
<P>
Cuba, Uruguay and Venezuela were eliminated during the second
round. In the preliminary round, Mexico and the Dominican Republic
wer 76-75 in a match to decide who took third place in the
standings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
