<HEADLINE> Fujian Attracts More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 1 (Xinhua)-- Fujian province in east China,
the ancestral home to over eight million overseas Chinese,
absorbed an investment of 1.83 billion U.S. dollars from abroad
during the first half of this year, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
This figure was a 20.6 percent increase over the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
An investment and trade fair will open in Xiamen, the
province's only Special Economic Zone, on September 8.
</P>
<P>
Businessmen from more than 50 countries and regions will talk
with their Chinese counterparts in this State-level promotion,
which focuses on attracting direct investment from
overseas. 
</P>
