<HEADLINE> Thai Parliament Passes Ship Act </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Parliament has passed
an amended version of the Thai Ship Act, the local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The new act will provide more incentives, which are similar to
those in Singapore and other countries, to Thai investors to
encourage them to register their vessels locally.
</P>
<P>
So far, Thai investors have planned to register about 10
vessels in Thailand and each will be 10,000 tons or more.
