<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Rate Falls to 11-Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- India's annual rate of
inflation fell to an 11-year low of 3.75 percent for the week
ending August 6, the Times of India said today.
</P>
<P>
The current level of 3.75 percent, the lowest since the 3.8
percent recorded in the week ending January 11, 1986, comes after
a free-fall for seven weeks.
</P>
<P>
Inflation has come down by a whopping 2.1 percentage points
since June 28 this year.
</P>
<P>
In the reference week, the annual rate of inflation went down
by 0.33 percentage points to 3.75 percent from 4.08 percent during
the previous week.
</P>
<P>
Compared to this, annual inflation was 6.21 percent in the
corresponding week last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the wholesale price index (wpi) for "all
commodities" (base 1981-82=100) recorded a decline of 0.1 percent
to 326.5 during the week from the week before.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
