<DOCNO> XIE19970901.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Six-Month Thai Exports to U.S. Up 10 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Thai exports to the United
States in the first six months of this year totaled 130.42 billion
baht (5.2 billion U.S. dollars), up 10 percent from the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The increase was mainly attributed to the rising demand in the
U.S. market for Thai products, such as transformers, frozen
seafood, televisions, canned food, wire cable, computers and
parts, women's garments, frozen shrimps and jewelry, according to
a report of the Thai Commerce Ministry available today.
</P>
<P>
However, the Thai share of the U.S. market was only 1 percent
during the first five months of this year, slightly down from the
same period of last year, as the Thai market share declined for
frozen fish, natural rubber, artificial flowers, ceramics,
tableware and toys, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also noted that Thai exports to the European Union
in the first six months of this year amounted to 111.2 billion
baht (4.47 billion dollars), down 1 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
