<HEADLINE> Pakistani FM Visits Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Foreign Minister
Gohar Ayub Khan began a two-day visit to Thailand today, during
which the two countries will sign an agreement to set up a joint
economic commission.
</P>
<P>
He is the first high-ranking Pakistani minister to visit
Thailand since the two countries established diplomatic relations
in 1951.
</P>
<P>
The joint commission to be set up will look after economic,
commercial and technical cooperation between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Thai Foreign Minister Prachuab Chaiyasarn is expected to
exchange views with his Pakistani counterpart on cooperation
between South and Southeast Asia and the Asia-Europe meeting.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has consistently suffered a deficit in trade with
Thailand, amounting to 2.2 billion baht (86 million U.S. dollars)
during the first five months this year.
</P>
<P>
Gohar's visit coincides with Thailand's efforts to expand
export market westwards to India, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka and
Pakistan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
