<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Gets 5.4 Billion Dollar Aid from Japan in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka received a total of
5.4 US dollars from Japan under its Official Development
Assistance (ODA) from 1966 to 1996, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The ODA scheme had assisted Sri Lanka by ways of concessional
loan aid, grant aid and technical cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Under the loan aid program, Japan provided about 3.67 billion
dollars to Sri Lanka during the period.
</P>
<P>
This aid had been directed for the development of
infrastructure in various sectors such as transportation,
irrigation, electricity, telecommunications and water supply in
the island country, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Japan also donated 1.21 billion dollars to Sri Lanka under the
grant aid program.
</P>
<P>
Technical cooperation had also been extended to Sri Lanka by
Japan under which program about 3,524 Sri Lankans were given the
opportunity to obtain technical training in Japan and 715 Japanese
experts were sent to Sri Lanka to provide further training here,
according to the reports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
