<HEADLINE> Dini Warns Against Extremism in Middle East Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini today warned against falling into traps set by extremists in
the Middle East who aimed to block the peace process and called
into question Israel's "peace for security" policy.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Aspen Institute conference in Genoa, Dini said,
"Europe is able to distinguish the crimes of Hamas from the
mistakes of Israel," but this does not stop us from "recognizing
the reasons of the Arabs."
</P>
<P>
He recalled the words of Italian President Oscar Scalfaro in
July, "Friendship does not mean that the friend is always right,"
spoken in criticism of Israeli settlement policy.
</P>
<P>
Dini criticized the Israeli policy of "peace in exchange for
security" as an erroneous confrontation of two concepts. "It
cannot be said that there can be no peace without security," he
declared.
</P>
<P>
He praised the late Israeli prime minister, Yitzhak Rabin, as a
man who possessed "the great merit of understanding...that
security cannot be entrusted to arms alone." 
</P>
</TEXT>
