<HEADLINE> Bulgarian President Distressed Over Death of Diana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian President Peter Stoyanov
and his wife Antonina expressed condolences over the tragic death
of Princess Diana, who was killed in a high-speed car accident
early today.
</P>
<P>
"We are deeply distressed by the loss of Princess Diana," said
the president and his wife in a message addressed to the British
royal family.
</P>
<P>
"When a person as she was, standing as a symbol of youth,
compassion, charity and beauty, leaves this life, a part of
everyone of us dies as well," the message said.
</P>
<P>
It added that Princess Diana will be remembered for her charity
work to children with cancer and AIDS victims. 
</P>
