"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- East China's Fujian province, mainland's closest province to
Taiwan, is gearing on fast economic development.
</P>
<P>
-- China's second largest hydropower project, Ertan in Sichuan
province, will begin generating electricity in October 1998.
</P>
<P>
-- Shanghai started building a 630-million-US dollar skyscraper
yesterday that, when completed in 2001, will become the world's
tallest with a height of 460 meters.
</P>
<P>
-- Foreign investment in China will equal the amount drawn in
1996, which was approximately 40 billion US dollars. The forecast
represents a 10-billion-US dollar increase over the planned.
