<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seles, Williams, Agassi Advance at U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles of the United
States Sunday ousted Mary Pierce of France to set up a U.S. Open
semifinal showdown against fast rising compatriot Venus Williams.
</P>
<P>
The unseeded Williams defeated Joanette Kruger of South Africa
6-2, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Seles, who was famous for unflinching refusal to lose, rallied
from a thrashing in the first set by Pierce and put on her
aggressive play that few others can match before routing Pierce
1-6, 6-2, 6-2 victory.
</P>
<P>
The day had a somber edge as a result of Princess Diana's
death. A capacity of 23, 000 fans and players observed a moment of
silence for Diana in the Arthur Ashe Stadium before Andre Agassi's
match against Australian Mark Woodforde.
</P>
<P>
Agassi, who wore a black mourning ribbon on his right shoulder,
beat Woodforde 6-2, 6-2, 6-4 to reach the fourth round. Agassi
next plays another Australian and his first seeded opponent,
No. 13 Patrick Rafter. Rafter beat Lionel Roux 6-1, 6-1, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
In other men's third-round matches, Second seed Michael Chang
beat Sargis Sargsian of Armenia 6-1, 6-3, 7-5; Cedric Pioline of
France outplayed Leander Paes of India in five sets of 3-6, 7-6
(7-5), 1-6, 6-3, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
