<DOCNO> XIE19970901.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Ambassadors Should Return to Tehran: Italian FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dini said that after the election of a new Iranian president,
Mohammed Khatami, it was time for the EU to leave the diplomatic
incident behind.
</P>
<P>
The EU pulled its ambassadors out of Tehran after a German
court ruling on the April 10, 1992 murder in a Berlin restaurant
of four Kurdish opponents of the Iranian government.
</P>
<P>
The court ruled that the Iranian government had commissioned
the killings. The court ruling led the EU to break off its policy
of "critical dialogue" with Iran, especially after Iranian
officials said the German and Danish ambassadors would not be
welcome in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
However, German Chancellor Helmut Kohl recently said that
Germany was itself monitoring the apparent shift in the Iranian
leadership with Khatami's election at the beginning of this month.
</P>
<P>
The Chancellor said that Germany might revise its position on
Iran if the changes turned out to be "substantive."
</P>
<P>
Dini said that Italy would be seeking to accelerate this
re-assessment. "Solidarity with Germany has been shown by all but
now there is a new presidency in Iran. Let's start again and see
if Tehran sends signals of openness and dialogue, as the
international community expects."
</P>
<P>
Dini said the problem should be resolved "as soon as possible."
Khatami's inauguration earlier this month would have been a good
opportunity for solving it, but it had been missed, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970901.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Develop Hi-tech Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai will give priority to
modern biological science, the information industry and the new
materials industry in the next three years.
</P>
<P>
Huang Ju, Secretary of the Shanghai Municipal Committee of the
Communist Party of China, told a meeting here recently that
Shangha's goal for the development of hi-tech industry is, by the
year 2000, to make hi-tech industry's output value account for 20
percent of the city's total industrial output value and its
exports account for over 15 percent of the city's total.
</P>
<P>
Hi-tech industry had over 75 billion yuan (nine billion US
dollars) in output value last year, about 14 percent of the city's
total industrial output value.
</P>
<P>
The city is offering financial support to some major hi-tech
projects, and is establishing an investment system for hi-tech
industry and encouraging universities and institutes to take part
in hi-tech development in local enterprises.
</P>
<P>
It is also encouraging technicians to find part-time jobs in
hi-tech enterprises or to use their hi-tech achievements to invest
in companies.
</P>
<P>
Huang said that experts from abroad will be paid well in
Shanghai and the city welcomes experts from other parts of the
country to move to the city to work. The city government will help
their spouses find jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
