<DOCNO> XIE19970901.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albanian Refugees in Italy to be Repatriated by November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi
signed a decree today to extend by three months the repatriation
of Albanian refugees in Italy on November 30.
</P>
<P>
The first group of refugees to be returned will be those who
have abandoned housing facilities to which they had been assigned
by authorities. Those with regular residence permits will not be
repatriated.
</P>
<P>
Cases of unaccompanied children will be handled by the
committee for safeguarding foreign children set up in Prodi's
office.
</P>
<P>
Italian Interior Minister Giorgio Napolitano said the text of
the decree will be made public on Monday. He called for full
cooperation between Italy and Albania. Albania had strongly
pressed for an extension of the August 31 deadline for the
repatriation.
</P>
<P>
According to the Interior Ministry, about 16,000 Albanians
entered Italy this year and more than 10,000 of them held
temporary refugee permits after violence erupted in Albania in
early spring of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
