<HEADLINE> Slovakia to Obtain 120 Million Dollars of Foreign Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia today signed an
agreement with a foreign banking consortium on the provision of
120 million U.S. dollars in loans for the construction of a
super-highway in Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
The loans will be provided by a group of foreign banks led by
the Industrial Bank of Japan, press reports said here today.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the loans will be paid back in seven years
and the repayment can be extended to ten years if necessary.
</P>
<P>
As a result of a series of economic difficulties in recent
years, such as the shortage of funds and cuts in spending for
infrastructure construction, the Slovak government has strived to
get international loans to make up for the gap.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia's foreign debts had amounted to 2.9 billion dollars by
1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
