<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian FM Calls for Europe's Intervention in Mediterranean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini today called on Europe to take leadership in easing tension
in the Mediterranean region, Italy's ANSA news agency reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at an Aspen Institute conference in Genoa, Dini noted
that the Mediterranean region was showing "ever more acute"
evidence of "fragmentation...migration on a Biblical scale,
religious fanaticism, political and ethnic clashes, and fragile
new geopolitical entities."
</P>
<P>
He urged Europeans to mobilize the "great international
institutions in favor of the Mediterranean region, in terms of
financial resources as well as security."
</P>
<P>
Dini confirmed that Italy means to call a new
Euro-Mediterranean meeting of foreign ministers.
</P>
<P>
The region is "in some ways the most important test bed for the
capacity of Europe to act outside the limits of its own
continent," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
