<HEADLINE> Myanmar Successfully Perform Cardiac Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has successfully
performed cardiac operations for the first time by advanced
methods together with Singaporean surgeons.
</P>
<P>
The operations on four cardiovascular patients were performed
here by surgeons of the Myanmar Defense Services General Hospital
together with two Singaporean cardiac surgeons last weekend,
official paper The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The surgeons inserted a balloon catheter in the heart of the
patient, the report added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Myanmar specialists also successfully transplanted
for the first time a kidney on a 41-year-old woman in May,
according to an earlier official report.  
</P>
