<HEADLINE> 1997 World Gymnastics Championships Opens in Lausanne </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 World Gymnastics
Championships began here Sunday evening at the Malley sports
center in the Olympic capital of Lausanne, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
About 400 officials including President of the International
Olympic Committee (IOC) Juan Samaranch and President of the
International Gymnastics Federation (FIG) Bruno Grandi were among
5,000 spectators in the main hall of the Malley sports center.
</P>
<P>
Following Grandi's declaration of the opening of the 33rd World
Gymnastics Championships, Swiss gymnasts and artists presented an
hour-long variety show to entertain the audience.
</P>
<P>
A total of 438 man and woman gymnasts from around 60 national
and regional federations will begin competition in team and
individual events from September 1 to 6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
