<HEADLINE> Clinton Mourns Death of Princess Diana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 31 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
today went to church together with his family to mourn the death
of Princess Diana but has not decided whether to attend the
funeral.
</P>
<P>
"We liked her very much. We admired her work for children, for
people with AIDS, for the cause of ending the scourge of land
mines in the world," Clinton told reporters before he and his
vacationing family headed to church in Edgartown, Massachusetts.
</P>
<P>
"We can only hope that her work will go forward and that
everyone who can will support her two fine sons and help them to
have the life and the future that she would want," Clinton said.
</P>
<P>
Clinton was awaiting word from London on funeral arrangements
before deciding whether to travel to any services, local reports
quoted White House sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. will be represented at the funeral but who will go
will not be announced until arrangements are completed in London,
State Department spokeswoman Julie Resied said here today.
</P>
<P>
Princess Diana was killed in a car accident in Paris early
Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
